● Order of Evaluation 

int a = 2, b = 3, c = 4;
int result = a + b * c;  

Step-by-step:
• * has higher precedence than +.
• So b * c happens first: 3 * 4 = 12.
• Then a + 12 → 2 + 12 = 14.

Sample Java Code:

public class PrecedenceDemo {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        int a = 2, b = 3, c = 4;
        int result = a + b * c;  // Multiplication first

        System.out.println("Result: " + result);  // Output: 14

        int x = 5;
        int y = ++x * 2;  // Prefix ++ first, then multiplication
        System.out.println("y: " + y);  // Output: 12
    }
}
